                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13012242" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2011 21:47:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just sketching out an idea here. Using this and ROWCOL blooms helps an upsert-bound use case but there is still something else going on with that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13012286" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2011 00:18:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Running this under the profiler I find this change keeps the time for Store#upsert proportional to that for HRegion#getLastIncrement, at about 30% each for an Increment only workload. Otherwise the relative time for getLastIncrement creeps up to about 70%.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13012288" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2011 00:19:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe this shouldn&apos;t be minor priority.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014738" author="stack" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2011 16:52:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks fine Andrew but does seem like a bandaid for the issue you are seeing with CSLM.  You thinking of applying it with unbounded number for the default.  You&apos;d add config. on the CF-level for setting max?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13014741" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 1 Apr 2011 16:57:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes unbounded by default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me look at per-CF.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agree it is a band aid. I don&apos;t suggest applying the patch, just keeping it around if use of it turns out to be expedient somehow.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
